You can run it yourself with two terminals.

From the project root:

Backend
cd d:\DEV\LABACT2-GARCIA-WEBPROG\garcia-server
npm run dev
Frontend
cd d:\DEV\LABACT2-GARCIA-WEBPROG
npm run dev
Then open the frontend URL in your browser. Usually it will be:
http://127.0.0.1:5173/

A couple of things to keep in mind:

MongoDB Compass or the MongoDB service needs to be running.
Keep both terminals open while you use the app.
If 5173 is busy, Vite may give you a different port. Use the exact URL shown in the frontend terminal.
For a quick test after startup:

Admin login: admin12345@fragph.com / Admin12345

//FULL RUN

From the project root, you can run everything with:

npm run dev:full
What it does:

starts the frontend Vite app
starts the backend garcia-server with nodemon
A couple of useful notes:

npm run dev still means frontend only
npm run dev:server starts backend only
npm run dev:full is the new all-in-one command
I also installed concurrently and added the root scripts in package.json. I smoke-tested the command and both client and server started together.

So your usual flow now is just:

cd d:\DEV\LABACT2-GARCIA-WEBPROG
npm run dev:full
Then open the URL Vite shows in the terminal.


